-- Australia in Talks to Invest in Ugandan Oil Industry, Daily Monitor Says
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2010-10-11T06:19:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/australia-in-talks-to-invest-in-ugandan-oil-industry-daily-monitor-says.html
Australia is in talks with Uganda
about investments in its oil industry, the  Daily Monitor 
reported, citing Stephen Bohnen, executive officer of the
Queensland Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade.  Australia is seeking a “comprehensive agreement” that
will identify opportunities for Australian companies, the
Kampala-based newspaper cited Bohnen as saying on Oct. 9. Bohnen
represented Australian Foreign Affairs Minister Kevin Rudd at a
function, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala via Johannesburg on   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  